ia cash reporting it offers four main areas of investment management expertise discretionary investment advisory services including outsourced chief investment officers which includes asset allocation manager selection and portfolio construction using an open architecture approach fixed income investing in corporate and government bonds and enhanced cash strategies equity investing in small mid and largecapitalization us companies investment advisory services to k plans a fiduciary legacy wilmington trust wilmington trust was founded by t coleman dupont in  since that time we have advised endowments foundations and other notforprofit institutions on how to preserve and enhance their assets through all kinds of financial markets and economic swings over the century fiduciary commitment is at the core of everything we do for our clients it is both our duty and our privilege to provide our clients with a high standard of loyalty and care putting their interests before our own that history is very much alive today and wtia proudly carries the torch of fiduciary commitment to its clients our investment process provides governance risk management and fiduciary oversight which underscore the alignment of interests to foster sound decision making advice and solutions tailored to clients objectives risk tolerance and liquidity needs a dedication to prudent investing fulfillment of responsibilities as outlined in the uniform prudent management of institutional funds act upmifa working closely with notforprofit boards in cofiduciary roles implementation of legal requirements and best practices creating an upmifacompliant overall plan which includes key elements such as effective investment and spending policies the need to provide full transparency over fee structures wilmington trust is renowned for many reasons relationships highly focused on understanding what is important to clients we aim to incorporate comprehensive customized and costeffective investment solutions we be